commText: Mayank and Abhishek Sharma are at the crease. Mayank is on strike. Starc will open the attack
Starc to Mayank, no run, over the wicket, full and marginally outside off, no swing and Agarwal taps it towards point
Starc to Mayank, no run, 142kph, full and going away, hint of away-seam movement, Agarwal chases for a drive and gets beaten on the outside edge

Starc to Mayank, 5 wides, banged in short down leg, Mayank misses the pull and the ball curls after passing the batter. Moves to the right of the keeper and even a leap from Philip Salt is not enough. Five bonus runs
Starc to Mayank, no run, 140.6kph, back of a length, Agarwal is late to close his bat-face, gets beaten on the inside edge and is hit on the body. Can't steal the single
Starc to Mayank, 2 runs, 137.1kph, Agarwal backs away early, Starc sees that and bowls an inswinging yorker. The batter brings his angled blade down just in time to squeeze it through square leg
Starc to Mayank, FOUR, 140.2kph, slightly overpitched outside off, no major feet movement from Agarwal who drives away from his body. Times sweetly and beats the cover point fielder to his left
Starc to Mayank, 1 run, 143.5kph, fuller than a good length, Agarwal stays in his crease and guides it towards third man with a slightly squared up stance
Harshit Rana, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshit Rana to Mayank, no run, 138.8kph, full around off, knocked to mid-on
A slip in position
Harshit Rana to Mayank, FOUR, slightly overpitched, Agarwal gets forward to drive it over mid-off for a one-bounce four
Slip taken off

Harshit Rana to Mayank, no run, 140.9kph, confident appeal for lbw, the umpire takes his time and raises the finger. Agarwal is quick to review it. Shapes in a bit does this length ball to beats Agarwal's inside edge to rap him on the front pad adjacent to the leg-stump. Ball-tracking shows it to be missing leg! Successful review. Agarwal was beaten for pace on that occasion

Harshit Rana to Mayank, 1 run, 143.4kph, nips back in from a length, Agarwal looks to play a flashy drive through the off-side and gets an inside edge onto his body. A single stolen as the ball dies down adjacent to the pitch
A slip in place and Harshit switches to round the wicket
Harshit Rana to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 140.5kph, angled in from a short of length, turned to midwicket
Harshit Rana to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 136.7kph, extra bounce from a short of length, Abhishek Sharma slashes and misses
Starc to Mayank, 1 run, 140.2kph, length ball around off, Mayank Agarwal pats it to third man

Starc to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, 140.4kph, edged, dropped and four! Pitched up ball that swings away outside off, Abhishek Sharma drives sans any feet movement and gets a thick outside edge. Would have gone straight to first slip, Philip Salt moves to his left and sticks his left glove it. Not only does he not catch it but he also deflects it away towards the ropes
Abhishek Sharma in SMAT 2023/24 Inns: 10 Runs: 485 Avg: 48.5 SR: 192.46 50/100: 3/2 HS: 112 4s/6s: 35/39
Starc to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 142.1kph, very full, late swing from leg towards middle, knocked towards mid-on
Starc to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 138.5kph, extra bounce from a length, nips away a bit and beats Abhishek's outside edge who chases it for a drive
Starc to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, 120.1kph, pace off and Abhishek Sharma knocks it to mid-on for a quick single
Starc to Mayank, FOUR, 138.5kph, pitched up ball that curls back in towards off, Agarwal allows the ball to do its bit and drives sweetly to the right of mid-off. A good-looking shot
Harshit Rana to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, 132.5kph, short of length ball, guided to third man
Harshit Rana to Mayank, no run, 136.7kph, shortish ball outside off, Mayank initially wanted to duck but then decided to dab and then finally pulled out from playing a shot

Harshit Rana to Mayank, 2 runs, walks forward and across does Mayank Agarwal to play a pick-up shot against this short of length ball. Ramandeep runs in from deep backward square leg and dives forward but the ball falls front of him
Harshit Rana to Mayank, SIX, shot! 140.6kph, short ball outside off, Mayank stands tall and beautifully ramps it over deep backward point. Used the bowler's pace to his advantage
Harshit Rana to Mayank, no run, 138.7kph, in-seamer, no room on offer, Agarwal moves leg-side and pats it just wide of the keeper

Harshit Rana to Mayank, FOUR, 112.2kph, slow and short, Agarwal spots it late and plays the pull shot. Nowhere close to the middle of the bat but he clears mid-on and the ball has the legs to run away to the fence
Umpire review!
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Chakaravarthy to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 91.6kph, spinning away, Abhishek Sharma moves leg-side to go over inside-out over extra cover and misses. Philip Salt breaks the stumps and appeals for a stumping. The back leg is rooted inside the crease

Chakaravarthy to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, 92.5kph, Abhishek Sharma dances down the ground, he is beaten in the flight and then throws his bat on seeing the line outside off. Slices it off the outer half and the ball eludes the diving backward point fielder to his right. Streaky boundary
Chakaravarthy to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, 93.4kph, this one's right off the middle of the bat! Full and in the slot, Abhishek is down on one leg to nail the slogsweep over deep midwicket. 80m six!
Chakaravarthy to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, 91.7kph, shimmies down the track and knocks this length ball towards mid-on for a quick single
Chakaravarthy to Mayank, 1 run, 97.6kph, in-drifter, driven to the left of long-off
Chakaravarthy to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, 94.7kph, fullish outside off and Abhishek Sharma crouches to swing hard and deposit it into the long-on stands. Thumped! 18 runs off Varun's opening over

Summary: Overs 1-5 -- Starc concedes 12 off the opening over -- Mayank Agarwal given out lbw on 11, uses DRS to overturn onfield call -- Harshit Rana was the bowler, and it was sliding down leg -- Abhishek Sharma dropped on 0 by Salt, Starc the unlucky bowler -- Abhishek Sharma belts Varun Chakaravarthy for 2 sixes and a 4
Harshit Rana to Mayank, 2 runs, 138.3kph, moves leg-side to pull this short ball, mishits over mid-on for a couple of runs
Harshit Rana to Mayank, no run, 140.6kph, backs away to cut, hits him high on the bat and the ball goes to the right of the keeper
Harshit Rana to Mayank, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to Mayank, out Caught by Rinku Singh!! Harshit Rana strikes! 128.1kph, bouncer from Harshit Rana that gets big on the batter. Mayank goes through with his pull shot and he isn't in control of it. Picks out the man at deep backward square leg. The bowler stares and gives the batter a flying kiss, Agarwal responds with a stare. Anyway, KKR have the breakthrough. Mayank c Rinku Singh b Harshit Rana 32(21) [4s-4 6s-1]
Rahul Tripathi, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshit Rana to Tripathi, 1 run, 143.4kph, skiddy short ball that comes in with the angle. Tripathi looks to sway away from it and the ball rolls to third man off the hemlet grille. Given as runs, so there might have been an inside edge as well
Harshit Rana to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 140.9kph, stump-to-stump line, defended back to the bowler
Harshit Rana to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, a boundary to end the powerplay! Abhishek Sharma dances down the track, moves leg-side in the process and flays this back of a length ball over backward point
Timeout! An eventful powerplay and there's not much difference between CRR and RRR. KKR will look to choke the flow of runs with spin...
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Narine to Tripathi, 1 run, 93.9kph, fullish ball, drifting towards leg, Tripathi sweeps to short fine leg's left
Narine to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 95.6kph, quick and flat around leg and middle, defended
Narine to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 91.3kph, Abhishek Sharma sees the width and cuts, backward point makes a diving stop to his left
Narine to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, 92.8kph, spins in from a length, Abhishek Sharma reads it off the pitch and tucks it through midwicket
Narine to Tripathi, no run, 95.3kph, gets down low to sweep this length ball to short fine
Narine to Tripathi, no run, sharp spin into the right-hander, Tripathi moves leg-side to cut and is beaten on the inside edge. Wasn't too far away from the off-stump
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Russell to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, hard length delivery that sits up nicely onto off stump, Abhishek Sharma cuts it late and cuts it hard to get it behind square but well away from the third-man fielder
Russell to Abhishek Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Chakaravarthy!! can the man do any wrong today? Andre Russell roars as Nitish Rana comes closer to hug him, he's got rid of a dangerous looking Abhishek Sharma. A well directed short ball, Sharma tries to pull it away but ends up getting a top-edge. Chakaravarthy runs in and to his left from fine leg to complete a regulation catch. Both SRH openers out after a start. Abhishek Sharma c Chakaravarthy b Russell 32(19) [4s-4 6s-2]
Aiden Markram, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Russell to Markram, FOUR, another short ball, this one doesn't rise enough and it is also directed to a man who devours this length for fun. Doesn't matter if that's his first ball. Markram stays in his crease and smokes the pull in front of square, over the infield for a boundary
Russell to Markram, 1 run, on a length and wider, Markram gets a bit closer to punch it square of the wicket
Russell to Tripathi, no run, another well directed bouncer from Russell, was at the stumps. Tripathi moves his head to his left to get out of harm's way
Russell to Tripathi, leg byes, 1 run, length ball slanting inwards, onto the body. Catches an underedge onto the thigh pad and deflects to the right of keeper Salt
Impact Sub for KKR: Suyash Sharma comes in, Ramandeep Singh goes out
Narine to Tripathi, 1 run, off spinner from a length, onto the pads. Tripathi tucks it towards mid-wicket from his crease
Narine to Markram, 1 run, pushed fuller and quicker, Markram punches it towards deep mid-wicket from his crease
Narine to Tripathi, 2 runs, length ball at the stumps, swept between deep square and deep mid-wicket to enable a second run

Narine to Tripathi, 1 run, dropped!! An easy catch by IPL standards. Chakaravarthy took one last over, but makes a meal of this. Was a fuller delivery onto the stumps, Tripathi went for a big slog sweep but top-edges it towards short fine. The fielder settles under but never really looked comfortable. Bobbles in and out his hands
Narine to Markram, 2 runs, flat and comes on hurriedly towards Markram, punched behind square on the off side for a couple of runs
Narine to Markram, 1 run, quicker on middle and leg, pushed down to long-on
Suyash Sharma into the attack. Watch out for the googly!
Suyash Sharma, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Suyash Sharma to Markram, 1 run, starts with a full leg spinner, turned towards long-on

Suyash Sharma to Tripathi, SIX, flighted up on off, was another leg spinner. Tripathi read it well and went for a big swipe across the line. Over and to the right of Russell at long-on for a flat six!!
Suyash Sharma to Tripathi, 1 run, pushed quicker outside off, swept in front of square towards deep mid-wicket
Suyash Sharma to Markram, FOUR, flat delivery, sprayed onto off stump. Markram rocks back and clobbers his punch in front of square for a boundary. Towards the extra cover boundary
Suyash Sharma to Markram, 1 run, was the googly, Markram didn't read it and went for a big slog. Inside edges it towards square leg

Suyash Sharma to Tripathi, 1 run, ouch!! That's painful. A quick, full delivery onto off, Tripathi hits it at a million miles back towards Suyash Sharma who parries it onto the calf of the umpire. Umpire Rohan Pandit is down holding his knee, hopefully he'll be fine. The batters cross over for a single

Summary: Overs 6-10 -- Harshit Rana gets rid of Mayank Agarwal (for 32) with a short ball -- 4 dots and just 2 singles of Narine's opening over -- Russell removes Abhishek Sharma (for 32) with a bumper -- Tripathi dropped by Varun Chakaravarthy (off Narine) on 5 -- Impact sub Suyash drops a tough return catch off Tripathi (on 13)

Narine to Tripathi, no run, spins sharply from a fuller length. Tripathi played it from his backfoot and couldn't adjust. Strikes his pads and Salt goes up in appeal, Narine not interested. Ball tracking shows it would have been three reds!
Narine to Tripathi, 2 runs, onto the pads. Turned softly towards a vacant mid-wicket region for a couple of runs
Narine to Tripathi, 1 run, slow and on a length, swept into the ground towards mid-wicket for a single
Narine to Markram, 1 run, flat outside off, punched down to long-off
Narine to Tripathi, 1 run, fuller and outside off, Tripathi with a big swipe across the line. On the bounce towards long-on
Double of 50-plus score and a wicket in an IPL match most often 9 - Andre Russell 8 - Shane Watson 8 - Jacques Kallis 6 - Suresh Raina 6 - Kieron Pollard
Narine to Markram, 1 run, pushed through from a length, Markram rocks back and punches it across the line towards wide long-on. I0$
Varun Chakaravarthy [1.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Markram, 1 run, seam up and sliding outside off, cut square of the wicket by Markram
Chakaravarthy to Tripathi, 1 run, pushed fuller at the stumps, swept towards deep backward square leg
Chakaravarthy to Markram, no run, on a length, Markram steps out but isn't to the pitch of it. Punches it into the ground towards extra cover
Chakaravarthy to Markram, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to Markram, out Caught by Rinku Singh!! Gone!! Superb catch by Rinku diving forward, his second of the night! Clever bowling from Chakaravarthy, saw Markram backing away and fired it in near his boots, trying to take away the room. Markram cleared his front leg for a slog but didn't time it cleanly. Rinku from deep mid-wicket runs in and completes the catch with a forward dive. Big wicket in the context of the game!! Markram c Rinku Singh b Chakaravarthy 18(13) [4s-2]
Heinrich Klaasen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, no run, flat and slides onto the pads, Klaasen can't clip it away
A slip and a leg slip. Attacking captaincy here, wonder how much of this is motivated from GG in the dugout
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, 1 run, fuller delivery that spins in, Klaasen turns it towards long-on off the backfoot
Required rate climbs beyond 12 now.
Narine to Klaasen, 1 run, fuller onto off stump, pushed down towards long-off
Narine to Tripathi, 1 run, swept towards deep mid-wicket, across the line
Narine to Klaasen, 1 run, sliding down leg almost, Klaasen tucks it towards deep backward square leg
Narine to Tripathi, no run, on a length outside off, doesn't spin. Tripathi tries to cut it away but can't connect
Narine to Tripathi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Narine to Tripathi, out Caught by Harshit Rana!! spinning in from a length, gets a bit of extra bounce as well and that is the undoing for Rahul Tripathi. He got low on one knee to sweep and goes through despite that extra bounce. Skews his timing and hits it straight down the throat of deep square leg. Narine punches the air in delight, he's deserved this wicket! Tripathi c Harshit Rana b Narine 20(20) [6s-1]
A short leg coming out now for the new batter, and a slip
Review taken for an LBW. Spun in sharply, did it do too much? No bat, but only clipping the bails. Umpire's call saves Samad
Abdul Samad, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Narine to Abdul Samad, no run, fuller delivery that spins in sharply to beat the inside edge onto the back pad. KKR review but it bounced a bit more and would have only clipped the bails. Umpire's call on wickets, Samad bats on! Sunil Narine has gone through his entire spell without conceding a boundary in a game where SRH are chasing over 200!!
Time-Out. KKR were 113/5 after 13 overs.
Suyash Sharma [1.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Suyash Sharma to Klaasen, no run, googly, spins in sharply from a length. Klaasen didn't read it at all and it totally flummoxed. Luckily, the ball goes past leg stump
Suyash Sharma to Klaasen, 1 run, on a length, punched down towards deep point
Suyash Sharma to Abdul Samad, no run, googly, slides onto the pads as Samad played the wrong line
Suyash Sharma to Abdul Samad, no run, quicker onto off stump, nearly 100 clicks!! Hit into the ground towards covers

Suyash Sharma to Abdul Samad, 1 run, onto the boots, flicked towards deep backward square leg. Rana the fielder in the deep who runs in, gets both hands under the ball with the dive but can't hold on. A tough chance, goes begging and Rana seems to have hurt his fingers as well. Manish Pandey is on the field for him
Suyash Sharma to Klaasen, 2 runs, full on leg stump, clipped to the right of long-on but Russell stops with an athletic tumble. Saves two runs for his side!
Varun Chakaravarthy [2.0-0-21-1] is back into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Abdul Samad, 1 run, quicker and outside off from round the wicket. Slammed down the ground and on the bounce to long-off
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, SIX, flat delivery onto middle, Klaasen stands in his crease almost like a baseballer and gives it a neat swing right over the bowlers head and beyond the sightscreens
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, no run, sprayed full and wide outside off. Klaasen lets it pass but the umpire is happy to call it a legal ball

Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, SIX, flat and angling outside off, Klaasen gets closer to line himself with the ball and punches it down the ground. The timing is pure and the ball sails over Shreyas Iyer at long-off for a 78m six
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, no run, quicker and fuller outside off from over the wicket. Klaasen can't connect on the cut
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, no run, goes for a yorker length delivery outside off, Klaasen can't get under it. Dot ball to end the over, neat comeback from Chakaravarthy

Summary: Overs 11-15 -- Tripathi trapped lbw on 14 (off Narine), but no strong appeal/review from KKR -- Markram (on 18) slogsweeps Varun and holes out to deep mid-wicket -- Narine eventually gets Tripathi for run-a-ball 20 -- Nitish Rana drops Samad on 0 (off Suyash Sharma) -- Klaasen nails a couple of straight sixes against Varun
Narine going off the field, KKR get a sub fielder for him.
Mitchell Starc [2.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack
Starc to Abdul Samad, 1 run, fuller delivery onto leg stump, Samad clears his front leg and slams it towards deep mid-wicket
Starc to Klaasen, no run, good length and tight, stump lined delivery. Defended back to Starc
Starc to Klaasen, 2 runs, length ball at the body, turned towards deep square leg for a couple of runs. That's 4000 runs in T20 cricket for Heinrich Klaasen
Starc to Klaasen, no run, slower bouncer, angling across. Klaasen can't connect on the upper cut, a bit puzzled by that change of pace
Starc to Klaasen, 1 run, yorker, well directed. Klaasen stabs it out towards deep mid-wicket
Starc to Abdul Samad, 1 run, on a length at the stumps, slammed towards long-on. Superb over from Starc, concedes just 5 runs
Andre Russell [1.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Russell to Abdul Samad, SIX, half volley delivery onto off, was asking to be hit and Samad clears his front leg and gives it a tonk over deep mid-wicket. Need many more of these
Russell to Abdul Samad, FOUR, yorker length delivery, Samad stays deep in his crease to get under it and smoke it down the ground for a boundary. To the left of long-on
Russell to Abdul Samad, 1 run, Russell nails the yorker this time, stabbed down to long-on
Russell to Klaasen, 1 run, wide yorker, Klaasen tries to slam it through extra cover but gets an inside edge on it towards short fine
Russell to Abdul Samad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Abdul Samad, out Caught by Venkatesh Iyer!! full toss, just under the waist on off stump. On any other day Abdul Samad would have sent this into the stands, but when Russell is having his day out, even bad balls get pardoned, infact they fetch you wickets! Slammed straight into the hands of a waiting Venky Iyer at deep mid-wicket. An extended check for if the ball was over the waist, but Russell is fine and Samad has to walk. Abdul Samad c Venkatesh Iyer b Russell 15(11) [4s-1 6s-1]
Shahbaz Ahmed, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Russell to Shahbaz Ahmed, FOUR, short ball from Russell, Shahbaz shuffles inwards and swivel pulls it very fine. Over the fielder in the circle and one bounce four!!
Big over coming up, a gutsy call from KKR to chuck the ball back to Varun!
Varun Chakaravarthy [3.0-0-34-1] is back into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, SIX, pushed fuller and quicker at the stumps, Klaasen stays still, lines up the bowler and hoists it straight as an arrow for a maximum!!
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, 2 runs, Chakaravarthy shortens his length significantly. Klaasen doesn't get the timing on his pull and hits it on the bounce towards long-on
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, SIX, seam up and on a length outside off, Klaasen gives it a slap across the line and over long-on. I0$
Chakaravarthy goes round the wicket
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, 1 run, pushed through onto off stump, Klaasen can't get under it and hits it along the ground towards long-on. KKR relieved he's off strike now
Chakaravarthy to Shahbaz Ahmed, SIX, fuller and wider, Shahbaz shufles inwards and gives it a big heave across the line. Sails a few rows into the crowds beyond long-on. Third six off the over!!
Chakaravarthy to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, flat and angling outside off, Shahbaz can't reach it. Chakaravarthy ends with a dot but concedes 21 in that over!
Mitchell Starc [3.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack
Starc to Klaasen, SIX, slot ball at the stumps, Starc undercooks his yorker. Klaasen gets under it and hoists it across the line over deep mid-wicket. Game still on!!
Starc to Klaasen, no run, full and angling across outside off, a big swing and a miss for Klaasen
Starc to Klaasen, wide, Starc goes wide yorker from round the wicket. Just a bit too wide according to the umpire
Starc to Klaasen, SIX, pace off, on a length and angling into the arc of Klaasen. He stays in his crease and whacks it over deep mid-wicket. Lot of muscle behind that one, Klaasen keeping SRH alive

Starc to Klaasen, SIX, that's a 25 ball fifty for Heinrich Klaasen!! He's back being every bowler's nightmare in the IPL. A wide yorker from Starc, slightly undercooked and Klaasen gets under it to hoist it over extra cover for a sixer.
Starc to Klaasen, 1 run, better from Starc, gets it closer to being a yorker and at the boots. Dug out towards long-on

Starc to Shahbaz Ahmed, SIX, that's the nearly 25 crore man you're playing Shahbaz, show him some respect!! A disdain sweep over deep square leg all the way for six as Starc ends up dishing out a low full toss. Just 13 needed off the last over, what a turnaround
Harshit Rana [3.0-0-25-1] is back into the attack

Harshit Rana to Klaasen, SIX, dug short and angling onto the body, Klaasen angles his body slightly and very effortlessly pulls it over deep backward square leg for a maximum. Just 7 needed now, what an incredible turnaround!
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, 1 run, slower delivery just outside off, Klaasen goes for a big slog but inside edges it onto his pads. Single taken
Some glum faces in the KKR dugout now. Who would have seen this coming?
Harshit Rana to Shahbaz Ahmed, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! Gone!! Length ball, hits the deck hard onto off stump. Shahbaz goes for a slam across the line but hits it straight to Shreyas Iyer at long-on. This match can still go both ways. Shahbaz Ahmed c Shreyas Iyer b Harshit Rana 16(5) [4s-1 6s-2]
Right, who's holding their nerve now?
Marco Jansen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana to Marco Jansen, 1 run, length ball, slammed down towards deep mid-wicket. Just a single but it is a single that puts Klaasen on strike
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to Klaasen, out Caught by Suyash Sharma!! Is that a bird? Is that a plane? Nope, that's a flying Suyash Sharma who's probably titled the game in favour of his side. A superb flying catch running backwards from short third to dismiss Heinrich Klaasen. A full, pace off delivery and Klaasen went for a big slog once again. Gets a leading edge that goes over the infied but the impact sub runs back, steadies and dives perfectly. Harshit Rana gives the batter a bit of a sendoff, he's charged up!! Klaasen c Suyash Sharma b Harshit Rana 63(29) [6s-8]
Pat Cummins, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshit Rana to Cummins, no run, I0$ A slower delivery outside off, Cummins shuffles in for a big swing at it but can't connect. Collected by the keeper and Harshit Rana celebrates. He's kept his nerve and given KKR a win at home. Eden Gardens goes berserk!

23:25 Local Time, 17:55 GMT, 23:25 IST: I0$ Gambhir back in the dugout, Russell back to smoking it out of Eden for fun, and Sunil Narine delivering miserly spells where he’s sneaking in a couple of wickets as well. And their bowlers are holding their nerve to eke out wins out of nervy situations. Simpler times, weren't they? This game shouldn't have gotten so close after KKR made 208 thanks to a fiery knock from Dre Russ, sprinkled with a Salt fifty that charred out Cummins' SRH. The visitors started brightly, as Agarwal and Abhishek Sharma both got starts, but both fell after scoring 32 runs. The KKR spinners choked the batters in the middle phase, as Narine escaped without conceding a boundary in his whole spell, while picking the wicket of Rahul Tripathi. It was looking like a routine win, but Heinrich Klaasen gave the hosts some worries as he took down Chakaravarthy's final over for 21 runs. Klaasen and Shahbaz then attacked Starc, smoking him for 26 runs in the penultimate over. Needing 60 off the final three overs, SRH got the equation down to 13 off the last one, but Harshit Rana held his own to give KKR two points in this thriller. Stick on for the presentations.

Ramandeep Singh: I was really enjoying my time in the middle and just to play with intent and that was the plan. Want to thank Gauti bhai (Gambhir) and Abhishek bhai (Nayar), the way these guys backed me really helped my confidence. The plan from the outside (message from the dressing room for the final over) was to take the pace off as Klaasen was hitting anything that had pace and it worked really well. Really loved the atmosphere in the ground, really electrifying and hope we win like this.

Pat Cummins: Close game in the end, wonderful game of cricket. Unfortunately didn't go our way. I thought for the most part, really happy with how we bowled. Obviously Dre Russ at the end there does what Dre Russ does, he's pretty hard to contain. Overall, I thought we did a pretty good job. You do your planning, you try to execute your best but a pretty tough guy to bowl to, played some good shots, couple of balls maybe we could have bowled a little bit differently but toughest job in cricket is bowling at someone like that in the end. It's one of those, goes one way or the other, amazing job by Klaas (Klaasen) and Shahbaz to get us back into the game and get us into that position. Who would have thought we'd get that close. Unfortunately a little bit too much. In a game where we didn't really pull it all together, we still almost competed against a very good side at their home venue, lots to be encouraged by, lot of good performers, a couple of points to work on also. Happy with how the toss went.

Shreyas Iyer: Right from the 17th over, had butterflies in my stomach. Felt anything could happen in the last over. They needed 13 runs and we didn't have the most experienced bowler. But I had the belief in him, and I told him to back himself and it doesn't matter what happens. He was a bit nervous coming in, and I just looked him in the eye and told him 'this is your moment, buddy.' Told him to back himself and doesn't matter what happens in the game. (On Russell and Narine) They have such experience. Great to see Andre perform with bat and ball, and even Sunny (Narine) was splendid with the ball. Fantastic to have them around. Always gives you motivation when you start with a win. This game also gives us a lot of learnings, there is a lot we will take from this ground. I think fielding is an area we need to improve on. It was so loud out there, it was difficult to signal to the other players from the deep.

Andre Russell | Player of the Match: Not really, sometimes stuff pop on my Insta and I realise how well I am striking the ball. Shows that you are doing well. I have tried to react with whatever comes my way. Over the last 2 years, bowlers have their plans against me. I have been digging out the runs, and I know everyone has a plan for me. (On his journey with KKR) I was on the bench early on, and just tried to make myself useful. This franchise means a lot to me, what I did tonight was just a way to prove what this jersey means to me. Hopefully I can keep performing this way. (On Harshit Rana) Shows a lot about his character. He told me he wanted the last over, he claimed it and he came back strong after the first ball went for six.

Harshit Rana blew an uninstigated flying kiss as a send off to Mayank Agarwal earlier in the day. Many might call that as snooty and borderline crass, but perhaps it is that brash attitude which gives someone the self confidence to defend 13 runs in a final over against a charged up Heinrich Klaasen, after getting hit for six first up. He is a Delhi boy after all, and given the track record of what ‘arrogant’, self confident Delhi boys can conjure up on the cricket field, we'd say keep it coming, Harshit! Another home win in the IPL, a winning start for a returning Shreyas Iyer and Gautam Gambhir. That’s all for now, time to blow a flying kiss and call it a night. This is Saurabh Shankar signing off on behalf on Raju Peethala, Abhinand Raghavendran and Praveen Kumar.
